  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean package)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Evidence carries explicitly-low confidence scores and wide uncertainty bounds in several validation activities; these are documented honestly with detailed rationale. The decision accepts the residual uncertainty as consistent with MRL 2 requirements given corroborating experimental data and conservative acceptance criteria.",
